1
00:00:02,147 --> 00:00:03,562
Nuit d'Or?

2
00:00:09,223 --> 00:00:10,787
Nuit d'Or!

3
00:00:13,799 --> 00:00:15,991
It's no use hiding.

4
00:00:17,152 --> 00:00:19,273
I know you're here.

5
00:00:21,795 --> 00:00:23,439
It's me!

6
00:00:24,021 --> 00:00:25,842
Michel Fournier.

7
00:00:27,044 --> 00:00:29,270
Michel Fournier!

8
00:00:31,739 --> 00:00:33,646
I'm all right.

9
00:00:34,273 --> 00:00:36,762
I'm starting all over again!

10
00:00:38,074 --> 00:00:39,787
And this time,

11
00:00:40,397 --> 00:00:42,298
I will win.

12
00:00:43,673 --> 00:00:46,351
So you can shuffle the cards!

13
00:00:50,410 --> 00:00:53,104
Make the roulette wheels spin!

14
00:03:50,508 --> 00:03:52,169
"Thank you...

15
00:03:52,791 --> 00:03:54,687
"Thank you, Mr...

16
00:03:55,168 --> 00:03:56,783
"Mr Private Secretary...

17
00:03:56,982 --> 00:03:59,992
"for the kind words
you were good enough...

18
00:04:00,679 --> 00:04:02,129
"to apply to me."

19
00:04:02,526 --> 00:04:04,276
And...

20
00:04:44,683 --> 00:04:46,704
"I'm not dead and you know it.

21
00:04:47,001 --> 00:04:49,912
"You burnt me alive.
I'm rising from the ashes.

22
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,478
"Michel."

23
00:05:36,926 --> 00:05:37,903
Hello?

24
00:05:38,193 --> 00:05:39,655
Did I wake you?

25
00:05:39,997 --> 00:05:41,861
You're a heavy sleeper.

26
00:05:42,209 --> 00:05:45,076
- I've called you many times.
- Is this a joke?

27
00:05:45,506 --> 00:05:47,207
I'm back.

28
00:05:47,709 --> 00:05:48,783
Hello?

29
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:50,883
Are you still there?

30
00:05:51,285 --> 00:05:52,872
I'm not dead.

31
00:05:53,317 --> 00:05:55,943
You have burnt my body
but I'm not dead.

32
00:05:56,649 --> 00:05:58,375
- Michel?
- Yes.

33
00:06:02,664 --> 00:06:04,353
But what does this mean?

34
00:06:04,685 --> 00:06:06,756
- Where are you?
- I'm here.

35
00:06:07,298 --> 00:06:08,656
Nearby.

36
00:06:08,953 --> 00:06:10,597
I see you.

37
00:06:10,916 --> 00:06:12,720
Go to the window.

38
00:06:13,179 --> 00:06:14,880
With the phone.

39
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:16,990
The wire is long enough.

40
00:07:19,707 --> 00:07:22,095
MICHEL FOURNIER DEAD

41
00:08:05,221 --> 00:08:07,699
Do you recognize him,
Superintendent?

42
00:08:16,387 --> 00:08:18,568
It's your brother.

43
00:08:19,300 --> 00:08:20,420
Please don't.

44
00:08:22,198 --> 00:08:24,025
It's awful.

45
00:09:00,827 --> 00:09:01,809
Hello, sir.

46
00:09:01,929 --> 00:09:04,161
A man gave me this for you.
It's very urgent.

47
00:09:04,439 --> 00:09:05,891
Good bye.

48
00:09:50,671 --> 00:09:53,103
No crime remains unpunished.

49
00:09:55,285 --> 00:09:58,699
You should know that, Henri,
my dear brother.

50
00:10:26,603 --> 00:10:27,665
Henri?

51
00:10:28,014 --> 00:10:29,902
It's Michel's voice.

52
00:10:33,327 --> 00:10:35,068
Michel?

53
00:10:48,237 --> 00:10:49,704
Mummy!

54
00:11:02,137 --> 00:11:03,798
What's happening?

55
00:11:05,214 --> 00:11:06,852
Nothing, sweetie.

56
00:11:08,642 --> 00:11:10,251
Go back to sleep.

57
00:11:12,067 --> 00:11:13,534
That's nothing.

58
00:11:48,198 --> 00:11:49,762
Michel.

59
00:12:55,988 --> 00:12:57,438
Mummy.

60
00:13:01,421 --> 00:13:03,345
Mummy...

61
00:13:12,085 --> 00:13:13,901
Mummy, wake up.

62
00:13:35,896 --> 00:13:37,300
That's it.

63
00:13:37,914 --> 00:13:39,472
Sleep.

64
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:42,866
Sleep...

65
00:13:46,810 --> 00:13:49,208
One day, you won't wake up.

66
00:13:53,781 --> 00:13:56,179
One day, you won't wake up.

67
00:14:04,414 --> 00:14:05,698
Hello?

68
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:08,291
Clinique des Amandiers?

69
00:14:09,384 --> 00:14:11,359
Superintendent Pidoux speaking.

70
00:14:12,113 --> 00:14:13,871
Ah, it's you. Hello.

71
00:14:15,278 --> 00:14:16,947
How is my wife?

72
00:14:18,592 --> 00:14:20,328
Did she eat?

73
00:14:21,344 --> 00:14:23,799
I know you can't force her but...

74
00:14:26,490 --> 00:14:28,169
And her sleep?

75
00:14:29,911 --> 00:14:31,521
Nightmares.

76
00:14:37,811 --> 00:14:39,946
She asked for Michel?

77
00:14:46,275 --> 00:14:48,171
Yes, I'm still here.

78
00:14:49,381 --> 00:14:50,751
Look...

79
00:14:51,014 --> 00:14:54,360
I'm done with everything here in Paris.
I'll be able to go to Lausanne.

80
00:14:55,696 --> 00:14:57,061
Yes, yes...

81
00:14:57,335 --> 00:14:59,332
Yes, she'll be pleased.

82
00:15:01,059 --> 00:15:02,886
Thanks for everything.

83
00:15:04,519 --> 00:15:06,391
Goodbye, Miss Blanche.

84
00:15:15,556 --> 00:15:17,634
She asked for Michel.

85
00:15:46,719 --> 00:15:47,929
Hurry up!

86
00:15:59,806 --> 00:16:00,857
Madam.

87
00:16:01,119 --> 00:16:03,014
Your husband wants to see you.

88
00:16:07,397 --> 00:16:08,779
Henri?

89
00:16:15,542 --> 00:16:17,461
Henri, what's happening?

90
00:16:22,628 --> 00:16:23,895
Henri?

91
00:16:27,896 --> 00:16:29,540
Oh, Michel...

92
00:16:47,119 --> 00:16:48,421
I love you.

93
00:17:06,624 --> 00:17:08,263
You're so beautiful.

94
00:17:11,384 --> 00:17:13,073
I saw her.

95
00:17:13,718 --> 00:17:15,625
She's grown, you know.

96
00:17:16,875 --> 00:17:18,724
She looks like you.

97
00:17:29,401 --> 00:17:30,965
I love you.

98
00:17:34,094 --> 00:17:35,350
Stop it.

99
00:17:46,595 --> 00:17:49,415
Your brother was dead for everyone.

100
00:17:50,043 --> 00:17:52,144
And here I am again...

101
00:17:52,954 --> 00:17:55,112
with my two sons.

102
00:17:56,865 --> 00:17:58,818
I loved him a lot.

103
00:17:59,423 --> 00:18:00,633
But...

104
00:18:01,138 --> 00:18:03,398
I never knew how to talk to him.

105
00:18:07,238 --> 00:18:09,271
We must forgive him.

106
00:18:09,758 --> 00:18:11,608
You too, Henri.

107
00:18:12,967 --> 00:18:15,205
There's a place for the two of you.

108
00:20:14,516 --> 00:20:16,504
Don't play with that,
you may hurt yourself.

109
00:20:25,092 --> 00:20:26,795
Michel is somewhere
here in the store.

110
00:20:28,206 --> 00:20:29,470
How do you know?

111
00:20:30,299 --> 00:20:32,540
I've found this in my office.

112
00:20:44,868 --> 00:20:46,479
I won't let Michel...

113
00:20:47,588 --> 00:20:49,343
destroy all I've got.

114
00:20:49,681 --> 00:20:51,570
All I own.

115
00:21:24,624 --> 00:21:26,231
Where's your father?

116
00:21:26,485 --> 00:21:28,225
At the warehouses.

117
00:21:42,407 --> 00:21:44,063
Tell me, Superintendent.

118
00:21:44,531 --> 00:21:46,152
Michel and your wife, Marie,

119
00:21:46,392 --> 00:21:48,047
were very close.

120
00:21:48,926 --> 00:21:51,232
- They were very close!
- So what?

121
00:21:51,645 --> 00:21:53,217
He made her crazy.

122
00:21:53,544 --> 00:21:56,529
Your wife set fire to
the warehouses to avenge him.

123
00:22:04,732 --> 00:22:06,099
Charles?

124
00:22:19,154 --> 00:22:20,935
Ah, here you are.

125
00:22:21,576 --> 00:22:24,425
Leave all that
and take this to the room.

126
00:22:24,882 --> 00:22:26,288
I've been waiting for you.

127
00:22:27,323 --> 00:22:29,450
I believed, like everybody else,

128
00:22:29,570 --> 00:22:30,916
he was dead.

129
00:22:31,991 --> 00:22:33,954
And all this time,

130
00:22:34,194 --> 00:22:36,180
he was around us.

131
00:22:36,534 --> 00:22:38,366
He was watching us.

132
00:22:43,519 --> 00:22:45,504
Why playing...

133
00:22:46,777 --> 00:22:48,650
this grim little game?

134
00:22:51,219 --> 00:22:52,927
I loved him

135
00:22:53,490 --> 00:22:56,721
despite the scandals
and the gambling debts.

136
00:22:59,891 --> 00:23:01,695
And then...

137
00:23:02,871 --> 00:23:04,755
there was the crime.

138
00:23:06,507 --> 00:23:09,236
The dreadful crime
in the Rue Duquesnes.

139
00:23:12,681 --> 00:23:14,611
No, no, no...

140
00:23:15,014 --> 00:23:17,878
No! He must disappear.
For ever.

141
00:23:18,278 --> 00:23:20,194
I'll give him what he wants.

142
00:23:21,613 --> 00:23:23,655
His return will cause
too much harm.

143
00:23:26,749 --> 00:23:29,163
Please, Fernand.
Find him.

144
00:23:30,538 --> 00:23:32,048
I will, Charles.

145
00:23:33,339 --> 00:23:35,550
As for the insurance,
it's sorting itself out.

146
00:23:35,862 --> 00:23:39,762
They admitted the possibility
of an accidental fire.

147
00:23:40,616 --> 00:23:42,740
A purely accidental fire.

148
00:23:43,421 --> 00:23:45,334
Marie has nothing to do with it.

149
00:23:45,719 --> 00:23:47,432
Officially.

150
00:23:48,489 --> 00:23:51,065
I'll never forget
what you've done for my wife.

151
00:23:51,327 --> 00:23:53,051
I'll find Michel.

152
00:23:54,337 --> 00:23:55,563
Thank you.

153
00:23:56,525 --> 00:23:59,070
We're not allowed
to forget men like you.

154
00:23:59,283 --> 00:24:01,961
Men who, with a deep
sense of humanity, have

155
00:24:02,326 --> 00:24:04,079
preserved the essential thing,
namely:

156
00:24:04,348 --> 00:24:06,029
the honour of the police.

157
00:24:21,057 --> 00:24:23,116
Thank you, Mr Private Secretary,

158
00:24:23,519 --> 00:24:25,622
for the kind words
you were good enough

159
00:24:25,942 --> 00:24:27,206
to apply to me.

160
00:24:28,370 --> 00:24:30,259
Thank you too,
my dear colleagues.

161
00:24:31,154 --> 00:24:33,458
This lamp you gave me

162
00:24:33,807 --> 00:24:35,994
will always be on my desk

163
00:24:36,479 --> 00:24:41,135
as a souvenir for the 30 years
I've been working here.

164
00:24:42,309 --> 00:24:44,687
Let's hope he'll be brief.
I am expected at the Ministry.

165
00:24:48,045 --> 00:24:51,901
You know the story of
The Phantom of the Opera

166
00:24:52,152 --> 00:24:55,109
who come back to haunt
the place he liked so much.

167
00:24:55,326 --> 00:24:56,490
Well...

168
00:24:58,167 --> 00:25:01,519
If one day you met
the figure of an old man,

169
00:25:03,157 --> 00:25:05,280
don't be scared by him.

170
00:25:09,333 --> 00:25:11,765
Another present
has just been brought.

171
00:25:13,049 --> 00:25:14,856
One more present?
I haven't seen it.

172
00:25:15,077 --> 00:25:16,755
Let's open it together.

173
00:25:17,216 --> 00:25:18,517
Sorry, I have to go.

174
00:25:18,637 --> 00:25:20,470
- Take care.
- Thank you, sir.

175
00:25:34,485 --> 00:25:38,127
What a strange idea,
giving a doll to a man of my age...

176
00:25:55,619 --> 00:25:57,018
Have you seen this?

177
00:26:10,666 --> 00:26:12,116
"My name is Marie,

178
00:26:12,426 --> 00:26:14,263
"the arsonist, the lunatic.

179
00:26:14,947 --> 00:26:17,038
"Meet me tonight at my mother's."

180
00:26:17,556 --> 00:26:19,229
"Signed, Michel."

181
00:26:24,619 --> 00:26:26,591
That's a strange doll.

182
00:27:34,738 --> 00:27:37,147
Here he is.
Like every Monday.

183
00:27:40,688 --> 00:27:42,140
Come on, Catherine.

184
00:27:58,651 --> 00:28:00,450
I saw you in the park.

185
00:28:00,873 --> 00:28:03,587
You shouldn't follow
the little girls.

186
00:28:05,301 --> 00:28:06,982
I haven't asked you anything.

187
00:28:07,501 --> 00:28:09,133
Of course you haven't.

188
00:28:11,926 --> 00:28:14,021
I recognized you immediately.

189
00:28:14,502 --> 00:28:16,320
You are Michel Fournier,

190
00:28:16,615 --> 00:28:19,180
the golden chain killer.

191
00:28:38,517 --> 00:28:40,758
- See you on Monday.
- Good bye.

192
00:29:24,371 --> 00:29:26,208
Do you recognize me?

193
00:30:08,817 --> 00:30:10,552
Superintendent Pidoux!

194
00:30:11,306 --> 00:30:13,492
How glad I am to see you again!

195
00:30:15,258 --> 00:30:17,074
Will you come and sit here?

196
00:30:20,628 --> 00:30:22,194
Like old times.

197
00:30:22,924 --> 00:30:24,294
No?

198
00:30:25,198 --> 00:30:27,405
You always used to sit there.

199
00:30:28,799 --> 00:30:30,829
At the table of the rich.

200
00:30:31,942 --> 00:30:34,201
You were a sorry sight.
A poor man.

201
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:37,810
The poor are not
necessarily happy, are they?

202
00:30:41,489 --> 00:30:43,542
Cheap ready-made suit.

203
00:30:45,279 --> 00:30:47,118
Imitation silk tie.

204
00:30:48,704 --> 00:30:49,989
Simulated leather wallet.

205
00:30:50,109 --> 00:30:53,025
You had lost before
you started to gamble.

206
00:30:55,649 --> 00:30:57,531
I know the face of luck.

207
00:30:59,256 --> 00:31:01,104
I also know
the signs of misfortune.

208
00:31:36,191 --> 00:31:38,172
Michel Fournier is dead.

209
00:31:39,212 --> 00:31:41,651
If he wasn't,
he would be at this table.

210
00:31:42,427 --> 00:31:43,952
And he would be losing

211
00:31:44,207 --> 00:31:45,848
as he always did.

212
00:31:47,241 --> 00:31:49,098
But he could afford it.

213
00:31:51,162 --> 00:31:52,937
Blessed are the rich,

214
00:31:53,643 --> 00:31:56,961
for theirs is the kingdom of debts.

215
00:32:04,742 --> 00:32:05,980
Watch them.

216
00:32:08,054 --> 00:32:09,192
Watch them closely.

217
00:32:11,963 --> 00:32:13,550
They win.

218
00:32:14,142 --> 00:32:15,707
They lose.

219
00:32:16,986 --> 00:32:19,097
They always lose in the end.

220
00:32:21,479 --> 00:32:24,019
They turn yellow, they turn pale...

221
00:32:24,848 --> 00:32:26,811
They wither.

222
00:32:27,977 --> 00:32:30,166
And they get old like their cards.

223
00:32:30,647 --> 00:32:32,142
And then...

224
00:32:45,010 --> 00:32:46,606
Look at this one.

225
00:32:55,567 --> 00:32:57,137
Has been actor.

226
00:32:58,297 --> 00:33:00,375
Old ham of second-rate play.

227
00:33:00,942 --> 00:33:02,618
Always playing supporting roles.

228
00:33:02,830 --> 00:33:04,090
In one word, shit.

229
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:09,751
All he earns as a TV whore,
he comes here to lose it.

230
00:33:11,686 --> 00:33:13,376
He gives me all.

231
00:33:15,688 --> 00:33:17,923
Old queen of the studios!

232
00:33:18,811 --> 00:33:20,573
Nobody wants him anymore.

233
00:33:24,782 --> 00:33:27,151
If I closed my business,
he'd kill himself.

234
00:33:27,884 --> 00:33:29,140
Enough!
Where's Michel?

235
00:33:31,645 --> 00:33:35,237
I don't like the smell of corpses,
especially this one.

236
00:33:35,449 --> 00:33:37,055
You killed him!

237
00:33:37,710 --> 00:33:39,181
They killed him.

238
00:33:57,575 --> 00:33:59,934
Michel Fournier is alive.

239
00:34:08,882 --> 00:34:10,860
Alive. Your hear me?

240
00:34:11,917 --> 00:34:13,641
He's come back.

241
00:34:14,315 --> 00:34:16,164
He shouldn't have.

242
00:34:17,931 --> 00:34:19,512
They'll kill him.

243
00:34:19,964 --> 00:34:21,094
Yes.

244
00:34:21,354 --> 00:34:22,921
They'll kill him once again.

245
00:34:26,151 --> 00:34:27,314
Who are "they"?

246
00:34:28,778 --> 00:34:31,039
They hate us.

247
00:34:38,978 --> 00:34:40,895
And you're the one
who'll kill him.

248
00:34:42,597 --> 00:34:44,456
You're drunk.

249
00:34:46,521 --> 00:34:48,553
Yes, yes...

250
00:34:49,241 --> 00:34:51,419
I am drunk.

251
00:35:01,700 --> 00:35:03,881
Why do you defend him so much?

252
00:35:07,046 --> 00:35:10,179
Men like you don't
grow old gracefully.

253
00:35:10,441 --> 00:35:11,801
Poor old fag!

254
00:35:17,312 --> 00:35:18,711
Cop!

255
00:35:24,285 --> 00:35:25,804
Hello, Mrs Jansen?

256
00:35:26,831 --> 00:35:28,544
Did Catherine leave?

257
00:35:29,115 --> 00:35:30,713
How long?

258
00:35:32,341 --> 00:35:33,951
Half an hour?

259
00:35:34,965 --> 00:35:36,666
No, thank you.

260
00:35:56,063 --> 00:35:57,330
Hello, Henri?

261
00:35:57,872 --> 00:35:59,562
Catherine hasn't come back home.

262
00:35:59,984 --> 00:36:01,240
Come quick.

263
00:36:01,707 --> 00:36:03,288
It's serious.

264
00:36:30,745 --> 00:36:32,720
You'll never see her again.

265
00:36:34,385 --> 00:36:35,993
Catherine is mine.

266
00:36:36,263 --> 00:36:37,713
Like Véronique.

267
00:36:52,722 --> 00:36:54,401
Your parents say hello.

268
00:36:54,823 --> 00:36:56,535
Especially your mother.

269
00:37:21,799 --> 00:37:22,966
I am Catherine.

270
00:37:23,165 --> 00:37:25,535
If you call the police,
the chain will be pulled

271
00:37:25,734 --> 00:37:27,123
and I will die

272
00:37:42,913 --> 00:37:44,957
- You must call the police.
- I'm begging you...

273
00:37:46,993 --> 00:37:48,615
He'll kill her.

274
00:37:48,951 --> 00:37:50,789
He's going to kill her.

275
00:37:51,720 --> 00:37:54,580
Like he killed the little girl
from the Rue Duquesne.

276
00:37:54,884 --> 00:37:55,965
She was 11.

277
00:37:56,184 --> 00:37:57,399
She was home alone.

278
00:37:57,813 --> 00:38:00,182
She wore a short dress.

279
00:38:03,810 --> 00:38:05,911
He came from behind.

280
00:38:07,162 --> 00:38:09,292
A golden chain in his hand.

281
00:38:10,988 --> 00:38:13,022
He squeezed very hard.

282
00:38:13,346 --> 00:38:15,096
She didn't cry.
She didn't scream.

283
00:38:15,216 --> 00:38:16,760
She had no time.

284
